text: [MUSIC] Last time on Trebuchet Village, we were introduced to Trebuchet Village, a village that existed long ago on planet Ebound. And the kingdom of the terrifier, a kingdom filled with orcs, goblins, trolls, and other nasty beasts that won a great war against the forces of good. Chief among these beasts were the Nards, terrifying furry beasts with yellow eyes, a terrible fanged underbite, six legs with talons on the ends of them, two arms and a penis tail that blossoms when they turn 18 and whispers dark thoughts in their ears. We also met our three heroes, Dogen the Dirt Goblin, Paladin and Dirt Enthusiast, Patrick Jodar, Master Shoplifter and nephew of a famous uncle, Evil Stevel, a vile cleric with a hip-hop edge. When they began their day, our heroes were just simple sales associates at ye olde Sullivan's General Store who moonlight as adventurers. They dispatched some unruly teenage grimlocks threatening their place of work, and then split off afterwards to perform their adventuring duties, which took them all to Mount Honestoodle, where the Crown Prince of the Terrifier Kingdom, the Nard Prince Jumanji, was celebrating his fifth birthday. For Nards, turning five years old is an important event, because the young Nards will perform their first kill in front of their community, and in this case, in front of much of the kingdom's important monsters and beasts. Mount Honestoodle is a mountain sacred to the Nards, prominently located near Trebuchet village just outside the royal family's home of Claw Castle. There, Dogen the Dirt Goblin was tasked with protecting the boy during this celebration by a group of paladins hired by King Nardwaur, the prince's father. Patric Yodar was meant to perform the greatest of heists by kidnapping the young prince in order to further the ends of the Sticky Fingers Guild.
